co.cask.cdap.api.dataset
Class DatasetSpecification

java.lang.Object
  co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.DatasetSpecification

public final class DatasetSpecification
extends Object

A DatasetSpecification is a hierarchical meta data object that contains all meta data needed to instantiate a dataset at runtime. It is hierarchical because it also contains the specification for any underlying datasets that are used in the implementation of the dataset. DatasetSpecification consists of:

  • fixed fields such as the dataset instance name and the dataset type name
  • custom string properties that vary from dataset to dataset, and that the dataset implementation depends on
  • a DatasetSpecification for each underlying dataset. For instance, if a dataset implements an indexed table using two base Tables, one for the data and one for the index, then these two tables have their own spec, which must be carried along with the spec for the indexed table.
    • DatasetSpecification uses a builder pattern for construction.
